(1+x)^{2n}>1+2nx
x\neq 0
x>0
(1+x)^{2n}=(1+x)^2(1+x)^{2n-2}>(1+x)^2(1+2nx - 2x)
=1+2nx + ((2 n -2)x^3 + (4 n - 3)x^2)>1+2nx
(1+x)^{2\cdot1}=1+2x+x^2>1+2\cdot1\cdot x
(1+x)^{2k}>1+2kx
 \begin{align} (1+x)^{2(k+1)}&=(1+x)^{2k}\cdot(1+x)^2 \\ &>(1+x)^{2k}\cdot(1+2x) \tag{By the Base Case} \\ &>(1+2kx)(1+2x) \tag{By the Induction Hypothesis} \\ &=1+2x+2kx+4kx^2 \\ &>1+2x+2kx \\ &>1+2x(k+1) \\ &\text{QED} \end{align} 
